inn1.comm: good length outside off, some appreciable shape away as Aslam ushers it through to another Yorkie behind the stumps
pitched up and straightening around off stump, 81mph and blocked int the covers coming fowards
drifts on to the pads, no swing this time, Aslam turns it gently to midwicket
again Willey angles the ball in and it goes on with the arm, flicks the pad and runs behind square... YJB chases it down and has a shy but I think Sharjeel was comfortably in
touch straight again, middle and leg, poked towards mid-on
that's a good line, touch short outside off, 80mph and Sharjeel hangs his bat out unsuccessfully
bowling over the wicket to the lefties, back of a length and on the hips, Sami nudges the first runs off the bat in front of fine leg
short outside off, not doing anything off the straight and Aslam swats at it, fails to connect
back of a length, 80mph on the stumps, nudged to leg from back in the crease
short and even wider this time as Aslam again fails to lay bat on it... The umpire doesn't like this one
pushed across in the channel and steered to third man
Jordan continues to drop short and Sharjeel slugs the first boundary in familiar, gunslinger-style, a flip-pull off his hip that Willey can't cut off charging up from fine leg
good length in the channel, 85mph and he lets this one go
on the stumps, good length and demanding a stroke, blocked coming forwards
on a length, little bit of width, Aslam opens the face and angles one through backward point
big shout for lbw, Sharjeel trapped on the crease as Willey snakes the ball into his pads... but he was standing on leg stump and that would have missed
drops short, Sharjeel plays that favoured Caribbean flick, forcefully but straight to deep backward square on the bounce
fired in on the stumps, nudged to the leg side
tight lines and Aslam again watchfully pushes away to the on side
good-length ball on middle and off, tapped down respectfully
nothing respectful about that! Short and whumped over fine leg for six on the pull! Lots of cheers and hooting as Sharjeel emphatically finds his range
slightly back of a length, stabbed through the covers for one... and Jordan has overstepped
decent yorker from Jordan, 86mph outside off stump, Aslam bunts it down the ground
short and wide, dispatched via the first-class post through point, a real bruising blow and Sharjeel picks up four more
better line from Jordan, 85mph around off stump, defended

oh dear, Sharjeel's tossed it away! Full outside off, he tries to launch Jordan over the covers, makes a proper Horlicks of it and manages to spoon the ball high into the air but only a few metres beyond the ring, where Stokes make certain running back
stays over the wicket, pitched up and prodded away on off
shuffles into line and dabs the ball down square
fullish, around the line of off, Azhar cold-flannels it into the covers
pitched up and swinging a fraction, 83mph and it draws a slight misjudgement from Azhar, a leading edge into the covers
presses forward and defends towards mid-off
good length on off, straightening a touch, Azhar shows it a straight bat - and that's a maiden
pushed across in the channel outside off, left alone
closer to the stumps, Aslam taps down into the off side
drops a little short, the ball is there to cut and Sami's eyes light up... but he swishes in ungainly fashion and doesn't connect
good length outside off, chopped into the ground towards point
on the stumps, again it's just the right length, Aslam can't really go back or forward, he opts for blocking
length, 84mph on middle and off, pushed back down the track - back-to-back maidens for England
bit of shape back into the right-hander, who defends on off stump
lovely shot, driven on the up, classical cover drive from Azhar and he's up and away
straighter line, pushed back towards mid-on
full outside off, Azhar mistimes his drive this time, plinking towards mid-off
touch shorter, 83mph around the line of off, defended into the off side
back of a length on the body, glanced through square to the man in the deep for a single. Steady as she goes
Jordan continues to probe away on a good length, tapped down into the off side
fuller and straighter and Azhar tries to take the long handle to it, miscues but the ball squirts wide of mid-on for one
pitched up, slightly wide and Aslam throws the hands through a slice over cover point, won't quite run all the way
tighter lines from Jordan, pushed back to the on side
goes for the big shot, trying to heave Jordan off a length over midwicket... carves himself a slice of air pie
touch shorter, 84mph outside off, tries to play it late and only manages to bottom-edge through to the keeper on the bounce
pitched up on the stumps, Azhar clips through backward square leg for a single
length outside off, Aslam opens the face and runs a single down to third man
pushed across in the corridor, drops back and guides one more to third man
angled in, 83mph on the body, nurdled short into the leg side
a touch straight from Willey again, this time Aslam works it off his hip for one
fuller, shaping in on middle and off, Azhar reaches out in front of his pads and gets a thick outside edge into the covers
pushed across on off stump, Aslam opens the face and steers the ball to point
straighter line, this time he plops it back defensively into the leg side
slightly short, swerves away outside off as Sami has another swing an misses. Chin up, lad

dug in short, he fluffs his pull but it sails wide of the bowler in his follow-through, he'll get a single to mid-on... but the throw to Bairstow is a tad wild and Pakistan are gifted an overthrow as well
back of a length in the corridor, rocks back and slides one to third man
length ball on the stumps, Azhar nudges off his legs for one more
pitched up and he flashes the drive this time, flies off the edge but it's in front of backward point
on the stumps and worked to midwicket
good length outside off, Aslam sits back and delicately deflects one more down to third man
touch straight and Azhar whips another single to fine leg
pitched up and Aslam marches out, scoops a drive over the leg-side infield, not quite where he was aiming but it lands safely
back of a length and turned off the body for one more to fine leg
touch short of a length outside off, tapped down towards point
angled in and worked to leg from in front of the stumps
full in the channel, Azhar unleashes the hounds (squirts a drive through point for one)
short ball, in the channel and dabbed fine off the back foot, just a single to third man
some seam movement back in, hits the knee roll... strangled lbw appeal but Stokes realises it was heading down
tight lines, wicket-to-wicket from Stokes, worked to mid-on
round the wicket, short outside off and Aslam steers another single to third man
shuffles across and turns one towards midwicket, could have been tight but they get through for one
full on the pads and Aslam flicks a couple fine, two there and up comes the Pakistan 50. Huzzah!
comes forward, punches an 87mph delivery into the covers
flapped slightly aerially but wide of the man on the edge of the circle, hitting on the up and he gets a single to deep cover
back over the wicket, on off stump and prodded to cover

gadzooks, a boundary! We haven't seen one of those in a while... This was a bit outside-edgey but he played it softly and the ball scooted fine of third man for four that was rapturously received by the visiting support
Aslam steps out and Stokes fires the ball very wide - too wide
slanted across the lefty from over the wicket - called again, though it was close to the tramlines and Stokes doens't like it
back of a length outside off, Aslam sits back and dabs straight to Root. The game being played in a very narrow channel right now
on the stumps and worked through square leg for one
pitched up and driven, not the cleanest of connections but it trundle into the stumps at the non-striker's end anyway
angling in and flicked through backward square leg for one more
shortish outside off, Aslam rocks back to cut but sends the ball to point
pitched up and prodded back towards mid-on, they scuttle through for a tight single
length ball, Aslam heaves across the line... and sends a swirling top edge to Stokes running in from deep backward square leg! The end of a fairly tortured innings
Azhar shuffles across his stumps
drifts on to the pads and Azhar picks up a welcome boundary with a glance to fine leg
on the stumps, prodded back
full and in the slot, thumped back down the ground - two boundaries in the over! Azhar finally gives it some licks, punishing a half-volley from Plunkett
angling in on the stumps, Azam works his first ball through square leg for one
tight lines, good length, turned to leg
back of a length, Azhar gets in a bit of a tangle, fends it in the air but short of midwicket... Root then tosses the ball at the non-striker's stumps, though Azam was in
comes across, dabbed down behind square
goes back and cuts, the ball screws away from backward point for a single
good length on off, Azam creeps across and defends
good length on the stumps, tidy stuff and Azhar opts for the clip to leg for one
banged in short, flying through over the ducking Azam
back of a length, 87mph and worked off the legs, into a gap at midwicket
good pace from Plunkett, approaching 88mph, Azhar defends towards his feet
Azhar drops back outside off and angles the bat for a single to third man
on the stumps, England keeping it tight, glanced through square leg for one more
fully forward, blocked out to cover
back of a length, but slow turn towards the solitary slip. Flat-batted to cover
clipped off the toes to Hales at mid-on, who was tempted to shy but opted out
swept hard down to Moeen on the midwicket boundary
on the back foot, clobbered into the gap at extra cover, where Jordan saves the boundary but fumbles instead to hand a rebate of an extra run
short and straight, more slow turn and chopped out to point
sliding down the leg side
tighter line, defended out to point
defended off the back foot to mid-on
forward and pushed to cover
blam! Straying onto the pads, and wiped over square leg! Timed to perfection, head over the ball and clean over the ropes!
forward to defend
worked into the leg side
misdirected, a full-toss down the leg side, and well gathered by Jonny
better line, back of a length, turning away and dabbed to cover
cut firmly out to point
short again but this one skids on, Azhar tightens up to defend to midwicket
premeditated gallop down the track, Rashid sees him coming, drops short, and Azhar defends
six No. 10! Down on one knee, mown into the stands with a violent heave across the line!
blocked around the corner to short backward square
outside off, good line and back of a length. Beats a tentative poke
banged in short, sliding towards the leg-side and helped round the corner with a measured pull
angled into the pads again, deflected into the leg side and that's the hundred up
short and hopping through to the keeper. A slower bouncer but a good tight line. Bairstow gathers and applauds
half-volley, driven hard, but straight to short cover
slower ball, angled defence into the gully
worked up to mid-on for another single
leg-sided, down on the sweep to backward square
outside off, slow turn once more, cut to cover
swiped into the leg side
swept hard out through backward square. Another excellent example of picking the length early and battering it
googly, dabbed to the off side for another well-judged single
worked into the leg side, sharp turn from outside off
good line again, this one doesn't spin as Babar waits on the back foot to defend
more turn from outside off, bat and pad together in defence
cut, in the air, Plunkett at backward point hops with both hands and pounces on a looping top-edge. A bit of extra bounce and it's bye-bye Babar
onto the front foot, jabbed back to the bowler
striding out to meet the ball, easy clip to long-on
worked up to mid-on
inside-out drive down to wide long-off
solidly onto the front foot
nurdled into the leg side and that is Azhar's fifty. It's been a steady but defiant innings, and he's got plenty left to do
googly, worked to leg
big stride, full face, pushed back to the bowler
worked into the leg side
attempted sweep, but this one doesn't spin and Sarfraz wears it on his torso
nudged off the toes and they call for an instant two. Good running
firmly swept, out to deep square leg
back of a length, nudged off the hip for another single
fully forward and blocked
premeditated sweep, dabbed behind square as the ball is met on the full toss
devious deflection, down on one knee and lobbing the ball over the shoulder with an angled blade
big stride, firm clunk of willow, Rashid gathers in his followthrough
a couple of strides and clipped into the gap past the bowler
outside off, and poked out to point
back of a length, hoicked out to deep midwicket
tapped into the leg side
another belligerent sweep, out to deep midwicket
inside-out drive to deep cover
the most delicate of late cuts, too delicate as it happens, as Sarfraz doesn't lay bat on ball
advancing down the track again, worked to leg
attempted nurdle through third man, but straight to the fielder at gully
flicked off the pads, backward square tidies up
wide of the crease, angled into the stumps on a full length. Jabbed back to the bowler
tapped out to cover, a well-disguised slower ball
met on the half-volley and crunched to short cover, well gathered
wide on the crease, deflected to point
spanked to cover, a tight over again
nudged to midwicket
another of Moeen's excreable head-high full tosses. He flings one in every match, as if it's a superstition ... free hit coming up
outstanding catch at deep midwicket! It doesn't count of course, but he leapt like a rabid salmon and pouched it in his left hand
tapped out to cover
turning into the right-hander from a full length
tucked into the leg side
big wind-up but an under-edge means that the ball ends up in the crease, not over the ropes...
drawn forward, pushed down the ground
back of a length, more slow turn, and Azhar mistimes his cut
tossed up, battered out to deep cover. Nice sounding shot, echoing around the stands, but just the single
fuller length, splatted back to the bowler

down the track, and Plunkett snaffles another blinder at mid-on! Sarfraz's frustration had been mounting, he galloped out to meet the ball but never quite got to the pitch, and his attempted mow over long-on scudded fast and flat, high to the fielder's left, who grabbed it in mid-air with both hands!
full length, met with a well-timed sweep, but Rizwan and Rashid collide in mid-pitch as he turns for the second! No blame apportioned, Rashid was ball-watching and didn't notice the incoming batsman
striding onto the front foot and pushed to cover
whipped into the leg side
back of a length, dabbed to midwicket
another dabbed single into the gap
onto the front foot, thumped hard back to the bowler
angled block into the covers, singles will have to suffice
onto the front foot, drilled to cover
patted into the off side once again, meeting a probing full length
slightly shorter, leaning back to cut but not timing it
that'd do. A touch of width, Azhar leans back and spanks it inside-out over extra cover. Playing with the spin and picking the gap in the deep to perfection
jabbed down to third man
eased out to deep cover. Six off the over...
worked into the leg side
back of a length outside off, hastily chopped to point
clipped to leg
tightens up on off stump
very full, attacking the top of off, and defended with a late flurry
anxious pokey defence, halfway onto the front foot, as if not entirely convinced he's reading the variations
worked to the leg side
solid defence
attempted cut, can't beat the field

big appeal and gone! Rizwan never looked convinced about what he was facing. And this one just drifts into his half-cocked front pad. Ended up playing across the line and he doesn't bother reviewing it
played with the spin around the corner
chipped in the air out to midwicket, Plunkett takes a pot shot but it's wide
whipped off the front pad, they hesitate for a moment then jog the single when it becomes clear that Morgan at midwicket hasn't gathered cleanly
eased on the up through third man, Roy hurtles in to limit the damage
down the track, chiselled to the leg side
round the wicket, shaping into the pads, deflected into the leg side
tight line again, can't get that one away
swept hard, in the air and met on the bounce at deep square by Roy, who has to watch the spin
outside off, chopped through backward point
tossed up, full length, drilled into the deep
punched into the off side, it's slow going ...
pushed into the off side from a tight line
a bit of a long-hop, but hauled straight to the man at midwicket
wider line, cut ineffectively to backward point, and that's another dot and another good over for England. Pakistan are going nowhere fast
round the wicket, bouncing up off a length to hit the splice as he defends towards gully
pushed through flat on off stump, stroked to extra cover
flighted, plays this with softer hands and gets it squarer, they trot through for one
over the wicket, tossed up on off stump, nicely paddled flat and hard through square, Willey scoops it up diving along the boundary
Azhar comes waltzing out, Moeen drags the ball down, turned around the corner for one
floated up and prodded into a gap in the covers
flighted, Nawaz nudges one into a gap
uses the feet, gets to the pitch and squires one through mid-on
pushed through outside off, Azhar leaps back and swats on through backward point

slogs to leg, in the air for a long time... but did it carry to Jordan? Don't think it did, he made an excellent effort to get there but couldn't quite prevent the ball from hitting the turf before his fingers closed around it
floated up and defended back down the track

comes down the track... and holes out to long-off! No debate about this one, Azhar looking to muscle down the ground, poor connection and it gave a simple catch to Willey standing on the boundary rope. The captain falls and the good ship Pakistan is listing badly
round the wicket, played to leg for one
angled in and there's a bit of spin as Imad sits back and defends from the crease
flat, non-turning offbreak on middle and leg, Imad gets off the mark with a flick
shouts of "catch!" as Nawaz leathers the ball over the covers, looked a bit like Rashid misjudged it out in the deep as he ran in but wasn't near taking the catch
tossed up and pushed into the covers
on the stumps, prodded back to the bowler
back of a length outside off, Imad absolutely smashes a cut but it's straight to the man on the fence
slightly straighter from Plunkett, swatted around the corner for one
length outside off, chopped into the covers
shortish, room for Imad to free the arms and slap one more to third man
on the stumps, 84mph and worked back towards mid-on
slower ball, gets this a bit wrong, bobbles through to YJB wide in the channel
back of a length and climbing through to the keeper as Nawaz tries to Babe Ruth it out of the ground and misses completely
angled in from round the wicket, nudged back down the track
touch straighter, goes across and works against the turn to square leg for one
pushed through flat in the channel, Nawaz drops back and slaps through point
tossed up and spanked down the ground on the walk, one to long-off

turn and bounce, Nawaz is a lonely island in the middle of the pitch and YJB completes the stumping! Moeen improves his analysis with the wicket of Nawaz, he fired this into the pitch as the batsman advanced, appreciably rip away from the left-hander and a simple job for the keeper
tossed up and prodded away cautiously - so that does finish Moeen's spell, a very fine 10-0-39-2
stays in the crease and chops to backward point, they think about one but had to scamper back
pitched up on the stumps, Imad digs it out to the on side
shortish, he backs away and crumps a cut, can't get it through
that's a good shot, finds the rope with a forehand smash in front of point, in front of the man on the cover boundary, right out of the screws
four more, larruped down the ground! This is the sort of thing the innings has been crying out for, Imad stepping out and using Plunkett's pace to crunch four over mid-off
fired in full, up towards the blockhole, settles for keeping this one out
short outside off, Hasan hangs back in his crease and swings in vain
on the stumps, shuffles into line and works the ball to square leg
short ball, well-directed... and Hasan takes a blow on the helmet. Maybe a bit of top edge involved, Jordan goes to see if he's okay. He is
back of a length in the channel and again Hasan swings wildly, can't lay bat on ball
short again, maybe taking the pace off, cautiously pulled down to fine leg for one
round the wicket, goes full and straight, whippy flick off the toes for one more - a good comeback for Jordan
pitched up and drilled down the ground... should only be a couple as David Willey runs across, only for the fielder to nutmeg himself and cost Plunkett another boundary
on the stumps, can't get this away through the leg side

smoothly done, ramping a full toss over short fine leg! Imad has got some spunk about him, he was pre-meditating this, angled the bat and used the pace to send it soaring away, just short of the boundary rope
dummies a step outside leg and then shuffles across, whips one more off his pads
pitched up and driven, not a clean connection into the covers
full length outside off,  Hasan strokes towards extra cover and they hustle a single to bring up the Pakistan 200, to much hooting and cheering among the Headingley crowd
pitched up in the channel, stroked through the covers to the sweeper
full and straight, Imad strikes it cleanly back down the ground, cut off at mid-on
oh, that's a cracking connection, another full toss and Imad creams it in front of deep midwicket, gives the boundary rider no chance
fired across the bows, dropped into the covers
stays back and chops into the covers, they scamper the single
Jordan goes for the wide yorker, comes forward and swished through point
Imad backs away but Willey follows him, squeezed into the leg side
back of a length, Hasan opens up his body and tries to carve through the off sided, find backward point
shortish, swung off the body to leg, backward square leg gobbles it up and has a shy at the non-striker's end... hits Hasan's rapidly whirring legs
dug in, Imad backs away again but mistimes a swat into the covers
he gets hold of this one though, short ball, roundhouse pull and it whistles to the deep midwicket rope
full toss at the body, scooped into the gap at midwicket and they rush back for two
excellent yorker from Jordan, right up on the bootlaces, Hasan can only shovel it back to the bowler off the toe of the bat
slashed over backward point, swings hard and gets it up and over the infield, third man cuts it off
fiesty bumper, beats Hasan for pace as he attempts a falling-away pull

wide yorker this time, 88mph and slips it under the bat as Hasan swings loosely, bottom hand coming off... England are actually appealing for catch behind, though it looked like a bump ball. They go to the third umpire but he clearly edged it into the turf; decent low one-hander from YJB, though
fired in full and straight, manages to bunt one through mid-on
Jordan lands a pinpoint wide yorker just inside the line, 89mph and Imad swings and misses

worked off the stumps, straight to midwicket, Hasan wanted one regardless and he's in trouble if Morgan could hit... but the throw misses and Root misfields backing up to give them the one they wanted
whammo! That's out of the ground! Willey misses his mark by a few inches and Imad lifts a big six over long-on. Turned out to be a costly overthrow
pitched up, not quite the yorker and Imad punishes him again, a piercing straight drive for four
bit of width, clattered through point, gives the man on a rope a real test but he saves four

length outside off and Imad again makes room to cream the ball through square, a couple more into the deep - and that's fifty for Imad, from just 32 balls, a thoroughly invigorating knock for Pakistan. He's been a real plus for them in an otherwise grim series
Imad wants to reverse-ramp, Willey sends a full toss down the leg side, he follows through with the plan anyway and gets one to short third man to keep the strike
slings down the full-bunger wide of the stumps and again it's judged to perfection, the batsman couldn't reach it but not a wide
full outside off, dug out into the covers
another decent wide yorker, squeezed under Imad's flailing bat: dot-dot-dot
pitched up and clumped through the leg side, past the dive of mid-on but just a single
the full toss does the job, Hasan slicing to backward point! The batsman was backing away to leg, swinging from the hip, flipped it high to Root's right for a running catch
on the stumps, blocked to the leg side and Jordan scurries after it - that's him finished, another solid death showing on his ODI return
oh, that's cheeky and it's also very good, gets the reverse-ramp away between gully and backward point for a couple
full and straight, clubbed into the leg side and they hurry a second
fired in full and slightly leg side, Imad was trying to reverse-paddle again, misses the ball - and Plunkett gets the benefit of the doubt from the umpire
goes full outside off this time, makes room and clubs a drive to the cover sweeper
slotted over the straight boundary for six! Gul is a powerful slugger and he picks up Plunkett's attempted yorker and deposits it dismissively back over the bowler's end. Have some
good length, fast outside off, and a swing-and-a-miss to finish the innings

inn2.comm: whoops. Well wide of off stump
back of a length, deflected into space on the leg side
lifting through to the keeper, left alone
outside off, poked to cover
banged in short,  but that just hops through to the keeper
speared out wide, on a full length. Jabbed to backward point with an open face

punched off the back foot and that is exquisitely timed through the covers. Not desperately short from Irfan, but then he isn't desperately short either. That climbed naturally from a full length and Roy was on it in a flash
inswinger from a full length, Hales closes his face on the drive, midwicket tidies up
clipped to midwicket, decent pace from Gul at 86mph
angled into the pads, clipped to short midwicket
lifting off the deck from a full length, through to the keeper
full and probing, fended away with a combination of bat and thigh. Squelch
well bowled, another attacking full length, nibbling back into the right-hander, and that's a maiden
good bowling, full length, angling across the right-hander, and just eluding a loose drive
full and lifting thanks to Irfan's cloud-scraping height. And that is an official warning for following through on the wicket
fractionally shorter, Roy's short-arm pull isn't entirely middled, but he places it in the gap behind square and there's no-one to cut that one off
crashed through the covers. Irfan floats this one up outside off and begged for Roy to fling his hands through the line. Oh go on, if you insist ...
gets it right this time! Perfect line outside off, climbs and leaves Roy, and Rizwan at second slip grabs an outstanding low chance, diving to his left!
up and running straightaway! Outside off, too much width and Root just flips that through point as if he's playing pinball. Both feet off the ground and up comes the paddle. Bang. Bonus Ball
opens the face, cut sharply to point
tight line again. Hales yet to open his account
that's the one! Right in the slot, a decent stride to meet the pitch and a full-faced punch through mid-off
another crunching drive, outside off, a rank half-volley, Hales opens his stance, picks his spot and clubs it along the ground through extra cover
back of a length, angled defence out to cover
short, Hales thinks about climbing into a pull but it curled out of reach at the last split-second. Still, it's a dot ball. He's back on message
right up to the pads from over the wicket, worked to leg
edgy but safe! There are two slips in place but Root finds the gap at third, and it was Irfan's extra bounce that saved him. A back-foot punch skews out of everyone's grasp
curling away, Root lets this one go
on the pads, angling down the leg side and helped further round the corner
outside off, too wide to tempt a stroke, not quite wide enough for the umpire to signal it
tighter line, fuller length, defended out to the off side, from the back foot
full length, nice shape into the right hander, compact defence on the back foot
that's a beautiful straight drive, just working with the angle back into the batsman, Root places his bat in the way, middles it just past the stumps, and no-one is stopping that
into line and defended back to the bowler
keeps a touch low from back of a length, Root adjusts well to dig it out
driving, but not quite to the pitch of the ball, inside-edged onto the pads
tight line, a touch short, Root hops into line to punch into the covers
defended into the off side
outside off, chopped to point
edged, but safe! Climbed into a soft-handed block and plopped a few feet in front of the tumbling slips
edged and gone this time! Another perfect example of line and length, angled in, nipping away, grazing the blade and this time it carries to the keeper!
low full toss, not the intended welcome, but Morgan defends it back to the bowler
keeps low as Morgan is beaten outside off. That's a wicket maiden, a rare beast indeed!
half a stride forward to meet the pitch, and defended to the off side
too short - not ridiculously short, but Root was onto it in a flash, Ricky Ponting-style, and pulling emphatically over the ropes at midwicket!
inching forward to meet the pitch again, defended to cover
fierce pace as Root wafts into a hook with the men up at fine leg. But the ball was through him before he could get there
back of a length, spanked hard to cover off the back foot
a gently inswinging full toss, angled out to midwicket
round the wicket, defended once again on the back foot
leg-sided, takes the thighpad and deflects to square leg
banged in short and a huge appeal for a leg-side strangle! But the umpire signals wide!

massive appeal, and there was surely a noise on that one as the ball fizzed through! Umpire Erasmus says no, but Pakistan are reviewing. Impeccable line to the left-handed Morgan, exploding past the splice, and the noise might well have been the back of Morgan's hip ... indeed, the third umpire agrees. Not out! And a very good decision in the first instance
dangling it out there, and this one keeps low as Morgan pushes loosely. Dicey times!
short, and a wafty pull finds nothing but thin air. That was a slower bouncer
back of a length, climbing into a back-foot defensive block. Another fine over
full length, floating into a front-foot drive
a fraction too short again and Root's command of length continues to astound. A disdainful pick-up through wide mid-on
over-pitched, an over-compensation, and Root rolls into a leg-side clip off the toes. Tremendous batting
good comeback, this one holds its line on off stump and Root's defensive prod skews out to point
on the toes, whisked to fine leg
patted into the covers
on the pads, tapped gently to deep square leg
onto the front foot, a gorgeous cover-drive from Morgan, he's off the mark and past 5000 ODI runs (for England and Ireland combined)
tapped to cover
round the wicket, onto the pads, clipped square
tossed up from round the wicket again, punched down to long-off
outside off, angled defence to gully
half a stride to meet the pitch and punched to cover. Root is daring the bowlers to drop short with his footwork

stays in the crease this time, and Root has picked the wrong ball to pull! Not desperately short, and Root gets a fat steepling top-edge, straight to Irfan at deep fine leg! The six in a row goes begging, and England are officially in a contest here!
tight defence on off stump
back of a length and skids into the pad flap. Pitched outside leg so no appeal
defended off the back foot to cover
outside off, a bit of a loose drive, and that hangs in the air for a while as it fizzes safely through the slips
full length outside off, Morgan drives from the front foot through point
on the pads, Morgan eases it with the spin to square leg
wicket to wicket line, worked back to the bowler
on the pads, clipped hard to midwicket
solid block, into the off side
on the pads, chipped firmly into the leg side. That's a tidy over, just what Pakistan need to keep up the pressure
outside leg, angling towards off stump, solidly defended back to the bowler
probing length, lifting into the gloves as Morgan defends
short, and a shovel-pull in front of square. Morgan did well to stay on top of the bounce there
worked to leg
on the pads, chiselled out to midwicket and that's a well-judged pair of runs to add to England's tally
outside off, and belted through point. Just a nugget of width and Hasan pays the price
angled defence to midwicket
too short, and Stokes swivels into a pull out through midwicket

edged, and gone! Catching practice from Morgan, a similar sort of shot that was getting him into trouble during the World T20, flat feet and a flinch/glide in the direction of third man, and it's a simple edge to slip!
outside off, a tight line to welcome the new man. Well left
full length, probing line, blocked solidly on the front foot
short and wide of off stump, close to being called as a wide, but Bairstow isn't tempted into a swish
on the pads, clipped out to deep backward square
off the mark with a squirty inside edge to the leg side
that is a beautiful strike. Stand and deliver, just shuffling early, standing still at the point of contact, and butchering a straight drive back past the bowler
full again, thumped again! Broad blade and full power, muscularly punched through mid-off!
outside off as Ali changes his line to round the wicket, angling back in but well left
solid in defence
Gul probes away on a good length, 82mph in the channel, YJB shows it a solid straight bat
slightly back of a length, Bairstow attempts to pull and gets a bottom edge into his legs and away fine for one. Not where he was aiming
moves across and pulls firmly through through square leg for a couple
length around off, tapped down into the covers
rising up in the channe, Stokes pierces the ring with a bottom-handed punch from the crease
full, drawing YJB out, he punches to the left of Azhar at mid-off and they pinch one more
round the wicket, tossed up outside off and driven through the covers
over the wicket, flat, skiddy SLA, Stokes waits in the crease and swats down the ground
back round the wicket, nice bit of drift and turn, Bairstow gets a leading edge back to the bowler
angled in with the arm, tucked through the leg side
flat outside off, Stokes leaps into position and hammers a drive into the ground, taken at extra cover
floated up on the stumps, Stokes clips to midwicket
poked back to the bowler who fields in his follow through
tossed up outside off, comes forward and punches through the covers
stays round the wicket, length ball outside off, tapped into the covers on the back foot
tossed up, that's in the Stokes wheelhouse, skips to the pitch and blooters it over the long-on boundary - only just, mind, but they all count for six
fired down the leg side, Sarfraz does well to cut if off as Stokes heaves at it unsuccessfully
darted on off, comes forward and punches one towards mid-off
drops back outside off and stabs to backward point
pushed through on the stumps, worked across the line to short fine leg
over the wicket, pushed through on off stump, drilled back to the bowler
rolls out the reverse-sweep now, fails to connect, scudding into the pads but outside the line of off
presses forward and check-drives through cover, past the fielder diving on the edge of the ring and they get two - England pass 100 in the process
pushed through flat outside off and Stokes is beaten trying to cut

flighted, spinning in past the inside edge as Stokes pushes on the front foot, thuds into the front pad... but appeal from Nawaz and Sarfraz, possibly just outside the line and Pakistan don't have a review left anyway
tossed up on the stumps, Stokes flicks through the leg side
comes forward and strokes one through mid-off
flat on the stumps, waits for it and nudges back down the ground for another single
drifting in, straightening on middle and leg, turned to short midwicket
tossed up and YJB presses forward to poke a single back through mid-on
skidding through outside off, Stokes rocks back and swipes a cut through point
floated up, comes forward and clips a single with the spin down to long-on
Heeeeeeeeeeeeerrrrrrreee's Jonny! Lovely stuff, dancing down the pitch, hits brutally through the line and it sails over the straight boundary
pushed through on off, tapped into the off side
quicker and flatter on the stumps, goes back and plays it late, forces one in front of square
on the stumps, Stokes stays back and works one off his hip
tossed up and driven, taken by the bowler but it was a bump ball
flighted on middle and leg, prodded back down the track

quicker ball on leg, Stokes flashes it over square leg, the ball just about carries to the man coming in off the rope... but Nawaz drops it! It was a top effort, to be fair, and it dipped late but he looks aghast at failing to hold on
fine bit of fielding at short fine leg this time, as YJB sweeps hard but only gets one
tossed up and worked back past the bowler
YJB comes forward and punches another single down the ground

dabbed to short third man, Sami Aslam fires in a direct hit! YJB thinks he's okay but the TV umpire is going to have to confirm it. Close but no cigar for Pakistan, Bairstow eventually satisfying Simon Fry that his bat was over the line
drags this down and Stokes lands a haymaker, swinging the ball powerfully away through backward square leg for four
flatter, on the stumps, tapped to the leg side
fired in flat, 57mph on middle and leg, hits the front pad
shortish, drops back and clatters a drive straight to extra cover
tossed up and worked to the leg side, again finds the fielder
crashed through the covers, the fielder - Azhar, I think - dives over it and the ball runs all the way to the rope. Four dot balls book-ended by boundaries
skiddy, length ball outside off, punched into the covers
stays over the wicket, angled on the stumps, Stokes clips through mid-on
shortish on off stump, 82mph and pulled, off the bottom edge, through backward square
banged in short, slightly wide and swirling away, Stokes doesn't bother to chase it
tight lines, pushed back on the leg side
good length, around off stump, Stokes can only poke it back to the bowler
tossed up on off stump, presses forward and drops into a gap at cover, scurries through
pushed through on off, slapped through the covers
flighted, Bairstow pushes along the carpet to extra cover
drops a touch short, punched firmly to the left of Rizwan at extra cover, who pounces to field
another firm check-drive coming forwards but straight extra cover
tossed up and driven, this time Rizwan slides but manages to misfield and they get a single - good tight over from Nawaz, though
YJB comes across and steers in front of deep cover for a couple
absolutely leathered, that's a princely drive from Bairstow, on to the front foot and slamming the door on a drive, flips the boundary rider the bird on its way past
length outside off, comes across and pats it down to point
in the channel, back of as length, swing and a miss
gets across on to the front foot and punches to mid-off
finishes the over well as YJB pushes to the infield once more
on the stumps, Stokes punches through mid-on
tossed up, YJB can only work it back to the bowler
nicely flighted, dipping on off, dug out back down the ground
pushed through a little wider and YJB goes deep in the crease to dab behind point
slightly short and Stokes can play his favourite, swingeing back-foot force through the covers for a couple - and that's 50, only his fourth in ODIs. Turning the game back in England's direction
errant, pushed down the leg side
tossed up on middle and leg, prodded back to the bowler
line and length from Hasan, tapped watchfully into the off side
bit of a powder-puff bouncer from Hasan and YJB gives it a by 'ecky thump over midwicket, a proper pull, I tells thee and it beats the man running around from deep square
drops back and steers one more through point
good length on the stumps, pushed back towards the bowler
dug in short, 80mph bouncer whirring away outside off, left alone
strays on to the pads, clipped round the corner for one
tossed up on leg stump, prodded back down the track
floated up around off stump, in the slot and into the crowd, Stokes opens up his shoulders and dumps Nawaz over the ropes at long-on
flat sweep for four, this whistles through deep midwicket! Stokes lands a one-two combo, the man in the deep given no chance by the power in the stroke
tossed up and driven down the ground for a single
searching line, YJB presses forward to defend
flighted, skips out and blocks back to the bowler
oh, how has that not bowled him?! Stokes goes for the mighty hammer over long-on again, misses and the ball bounces over the top of off by a whisker!
Bairstow comes across and steers a drive through point
tossed up and punched down the ground to long-on
round the wicket, flighted on off stump, blocked on the front foot
pushed through outside off, Bairstow slices a couple more through backward point
presses out to defend on off stump
pitched up, 80mph on the stumps, flumped down the ground to mid-on
full on off and driven crisply, Azhar fields it well at mid-off... but a poor throw means they get one anyway
nip-backer from Gul, he hits Bairstow on the walk, on the front pad... but Tim Robinson isn't interested. Probably outside the line
crunched on the drive but straight to mid-off
bowling round the wicket, 79mph outside off, waits for it and slides the ball past the diving backward point for one more
pitched up and plinked towards mid-off, driven but off the toe of the bat
pushed through outside off, Stokes chops through point - and that raises the hundred stand, at decent lick, too
length ball, comes across and pushes to point
tossed up, defended on the front foot
not far from sneaking on to the stumps again! YJB tries to force a drive off the back foot, the ball skips on, narrowly past the off pole
comes on to the front foot and defends
darted on the pads, can't get it away, just one off the over
round the wicket, defended into the covers
length ball outside off, Stokes pokes it into the covers
digs the ball in short, Stokes rolls his wrists on a pull
lets go a full toss, YJB flicks it through backward square leg for one more
fires the ball in full and straight, Stokes digs one out through mid-on
decent bouncer to finish, YJB crouches out of the way

slog-swept ... straight down the throat of deep midwicket! Stokes can't believe what he's done, a bit of pressure was building, he attempted to break the shackles, but picked the longest part of the ground to do so, and didn't wrap enough bat around the shot
over the wicket to the new man, Moeen, who pokes out past point to get his innings up and running
outside off, and chopped through third man. More edge than Bairstow intended but a safe enough shot with no slip in place
back of a length, angled into the pads, punched up to mid-on
into line and defended again
over the wicket, Moeen hangs back in his crease and works into the leg-side with a roll of the wrists
width outside off and cut hard in front of square. Another galling misfield gifts the single. They all count ...
tossed up outside off, a soft-handed jab to point and through they hustle
heaved out to deep midwicket. Another fumble. Nerves, dew, or ineptitude?
worked into the leg side this time
forward and driven to midwicket
short-arm pull to short backward square
over the wicket, and skids on with the arm ... Moeen was shaping to leg but had to adjust in a hurry to protect his off pole
forward with more certainty and defended to the off side
full face, an easy straight push back down the line of the ball. Mid-on gathers
lots of flight and a bit of bite outside off, Moeen reaches for a push to point

that's a dirty wipe through the line! Bairstow utterly bamboozled in the flight that time but luckily for him his back toe was anchored in the crease. Done for all money, and you can imagine the mutterings from Sarfraz under the lid
punched into the gap in the covers to complete a tense over
beautiful belligerent strike. Two steps down the track and crashed straight to bring up Bairstow's fifty. Top knock
worked to leg
back into the crease and easing another single into the gap in the covers
forward to defend out to the off side
round the corner, and dabbed for the single. England keep chipping away
shorter and wider, a firm cut out to deep point
worked to mid-off and tip and run from Bairstow, he's sharp between the sticks
angling away from the left-hander, and driven with an open face to point
forward and pushed to the off side
dabbed to point
round the wicket, and crunched out to backward point. In the air for a while but always safe
fully forward and thumped into the covers
angled defence into the leg side
attempted reverse sweep, outside the line so no danger of lbw, but Moeen doesn't quite make contact
outside off, driven on the up back to the bowler. In the air for a split-second but safe enough
attacking the stumps from round the wicket, Bairstow leans onto the front foot to defend
opens the face, guided out to deep cover
nurdled to third man. England are coasting now [cue clatter of late wickets...]
onto the front foot, defended
driven on the up, half-stopped in the covers, but through they go
worked into the covers
tight line, nudged back up the pitch
heaved down the ground, this is in the air for a while ... but Azhar can't back-pedal in time at mid-off! Moeen looking for the big release shot but that was off the toe of the bat
clipped into the leg side
jeepers, that is beyond wide. That was a good length delivery on the next strip! Mickey Arthur on the balcony looks like he's just sucked on a lemon-flavoured rat's tail
onto the front foot, driven to cover
over the wicket, that's a rarity from Imad in itself, and worked into the leg side
down the leg side, the fight has gone out of the dog here
onto the front foot, driven to wide long-on
pushes the single into the leg side
outside off, this one bites and turns past a loose prod
solid defence into the off side
back of a length, hauled into the leg side with a bit of an under-edge
short, and lofted into no-man's land on the leg side, a deliberate placement into the gap, and they hustle back for two
poked into the covers, more excellent running from Bairstow, who beats the direct hit by several yards
bashed on the up to mid-off. A bit of a hoick
short ball, too short. Moeen bails out of a pull
poked down to third man, another single
full length, targetting the blockhole and pushed out to point
on the pads, clipped to leg
nurdled in front of square on the leg side, and somehow that turns into two runs, despite two fielders converging.
clipped on the up to long-on
pushed into the covers
width, and cut hard to point
tossed up outside off, driven to cover, a pretty tidy fill-in over
pulled round the corner to rotate the strike

sharp work at mid-off, and Bairstow has run himself out! He backed his lightning speed between the wickets, but he didn't count on a bullet arm from Azhar! Now then, England putting themselves back under a hint of pressure
full length on the pads, clipped to midwicket
banged in short, and worked into the gap
wide angle from round the wicket, Moeen has a slash and a fat edge doesn't quite carry to slip. All a bit slow-motioned, but the pressure is on
defended into the leg side
on the pads, Willey stands tall on the back foot and works a single to mid-on
floated into the blockhole and drilled to cover
on the pads, that one spins but only down the leg-side and helped on its way
googly? Indeed. Well bowled, and respectfully blocked
down the track, driven on the up to mid-off
big appeal as Azhar beats a probing edge with another googly, but the noise was bat on turf. Well bowled all the same
round the wicket, attacking the stumps, defended from the crease to mid-off
finally, a boundary for Moeen, clipped firmly off the pads through the gap at midwicket
worked into the covers off the back foot
tight line from round the wicket, defended on the back foot
tightening up on off stump, firm defence
outside off, a cramped drive takes the edge and dribbles through to the keeper. Well bowled. Pakistan taking this deep, but England still very much in control
on the pads, clipped out to deep midwicket
in the slot, and that is sumptuous. Picked the length early, marched to the length of the ball like an occupying force, and pounded it over the ropes
onto the front foot and pushed into the covers
heaved in the air again, one bounce to long-on. England nearly home
googly, well picked and worked into the gap in the covers.

over the ropes, and that is that! Moeen brings out the long handle once more, needs a bit more bottom hand to clear the boundary, but he has plenty to spare. Pakistan fought valiantly to take it this deep but England's depth is formidable
